items.synopsis: New Zealand's All Blacks and Los Pumas of Argentina meet at the Stade de France in Paris in the Rugby World Cup semifinal. Follow all the action in our live blog.

title.children: New Zealand in complete control against Argentina in Rugby World Cup semifinal

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Far too easy for New Zealand. Another multi-phase attack from the All Blacks, Argentina scrambling to make tackles and defend their line, but overcommitting to the ruck allowing Will Jordan another single finish. The conversion is missed from the sideline, but that barely matters now. It's 39-6.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 62' Another try for New Zealand!

children.content: (Getty Images)
Far too easy for New Zealand.
Another multi-phase attack from the All Blacks, Argentina scrambling to make tackles and defend their line, but overcommitting to the ruck allowing Will Jordan another single finish.
The conversion is missed from the sideline, but that barely matters now.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Relentless attack from the All Blacks. Richie Mo'unga started it with a nice break to within the ten metres. Then it was wave after wave of attack, 18 phases of battering-ram rugby before Tyrel Lomax barged his way over. If it wasn't over before, it's all over now. New Zealand surely into their fifth Rugby World Cup final - and there's still 30 metres to play. Richie Mo'unga adds the extras. 34-6. This is turning into a horror show for Argentina.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 49' Try New Zealand!

children.content: Relentless attack from the All Blacks.
Richie Mo'unga started it with a nice break to within the ten metres.
Then it was wave after wave of attack, 18 phases of battering-ram rugby before Tyrel Lomax barged his way over.
(Getty Images)
If it wasn't over before, it's all over now.
New Zealand surely into their fifth Rugby World Cup final - and there's still 30 metres to play.
Richie Mo'unga adds the extras.
This is turning into a horror show for Argentina.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Aaron Smith take a bow! The Argentina scrum was going backwards at a rate of knots again - Aaron Smith got the pop pass from Ardie Savea, stepped off the left foot and burst towards the line - and could not be stopped. The worst possible start for Los Pumas. That might be the game right there. Richie Mo'unga is good from the kick and it's 27-6. When the clock ticked over 40 minutes Argentina trailed 15-6. Three minutes later on the clock, they've conceded another 12 points.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 42' Try New Zealand!

children.content: (Getty Images)
Aaron Smith take a bow!
The Argentina scrum was going backwards at a rate of knots again - Aaron Smith got the pop pass from Ardie Savea, stepped off the left foot and burst towards the line - and could not be stopped.
The worst possible start for Los Pumas.
That might be the game right there.
Richie Mo'unga is good from the kick and it's 27-6.
When the clock ticked over 40 minutes Argentina trailed 15-6.
Three minutes later on the clock, they've conceded another 12 points.
